reports.text: We slide across a slippery oil slick and nearly fall! Then another Racket Teen mocks us and attacks with his pokemon!
We make it across the large oil slick and find the robber from before!
We step onto the prototype warp pad the scientists in the lab created, and are suddenly warped back to our hometown! Cartridge Town!
We walk into the Russet Town Bike Shop and the store owner happily informs us that we're his 1000th customer! For this, he gives us a Bike for free!
Upon defeating {{$our rival}}, {{they}} challenge us to a race to see who will become league champion first! We readily agree (because we weren't given the option to turn it down)!

We walk into a woman's house as she is being actively burgled by someone in a brown hat and clothes! Everything's a mess and there's a broken TV by the door. The teen in brown looks like he doesn't know what he's doing...

We enter a parking garage in the south of the city. There had been a teen in brown guarding the door previously... a teen who had been dressed very similarly to that robber we chased off from that woman's house eariler...
There's a big oil slick at the end of the parking garage, and we start sliding around on it, as if it were ice.
We {{rand|slide|glide|slip}} around on the big oil slick.
We get spotted by another teen in brown! Declares this parking garage for cool kids only, and he fights us! The game calls him a "Racket Teen".
We engage the robber Racket Teen!
reports.wintext: We take out his final pokemon, and the robber none-to-subtly tells us to stay away from the Department Store...

We defeat the last of the Team Racket members. (yes really, Team Racket.) The last guy expouses about how prices for items are too damn high for them kids, and thus he is somehow justified in just taking the items in question. He says this before everyone vanishes and a cop without pokemon comes up to us thanks us for doing his job for him (yes, he really says that).

reports.text: We're suddenly jumped by some Team Racket teens, shouting at us to get out of their tower!
We {{rand|head|go|move}} upstairs into the winding administrative halls of the Guard Tower.
We climb up the stairs to the next floor and run into {{$our rival}}! {{They}} heal our pokemon for us, and then {{they}} head{{*s}} off to clear out more Team Racket members!
We ascend to the next floor, and run into {{$our rival}} once more. {{They}} tell us to take the right path as {{they}}'re going left.
{{$rival}} runs up to us and tells us {{she}} couldn't take on the leader, and that we need to do it in {{her}} place.
